880
00:55:22,744 --> 00:55:23,744
Your mom, and reporter.

881
00:55:24,504 --> 00:55:25,354
Yeah.

882
00:55:26,764 --> 00:55:28,744
Why do you keep trying to lie
when you know you can't?

883
00:55:29,654 --> 00:55:30,694
Then what else am I do to?

884
00:55:30,784 --> 00:55:32,214
I made a promise to my dad.

885
00:55:32,614 --> 00:55:35,709
I can't waste the rest of my 20s
as an unemployed bum. I can't...

886
00:55:39,064 --> 00:55:41,064
I'm too ashamed to face you.

887
00:55:42,394 --> 00:55:43,264
What?

888
00:55:45,374 --> 00:55:47,504
Do you think I'm stupid? An idiot?

889
00:55:48,084 --> 00:55:50,574
I know you obviously gave up
on going to college because of me.

890
00:55:50,664 --> 00:55:54,104
Do you think it's comfortable for me
to live off the money you earn? I...

891
00:55:54,744 --> 00:55:57,304
I have a sense of conscience, too.

892
00:55:58,124 --> 00:55:58,904
So throw these all.

893
00:55:58,994 --> 00:56:01,304
I feel much better knowing
that this is over.

894
00:56:01,784 --> 00:56:02,644
You're lying.

895
00:56:05,324 --> 00:56:06,174
Fine.

896
00:56:06,504 --> 00:56:07,484
That was a lie.

897
00:56:07,824 --> 00:56:09,374
